  "prompt": "How can I deactivate Quora?",
  "response": "If you wish to deactivate your Quora account, follow these steps:\n\n### On Desktop (Website):\n1. **Log in**: Go to [Quora.com](https://www.quora.com) and log in to your account.\n2. **Access Settings**:\n   - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **Settings** from the dropdown menu.\n3. **Deactivate Account**:\n   - Scroll down to the **Privacy** section.\n   - Click on **Deactivate Account**.\n4. **Confirm Deactivation**:\n   - Read the information about what deactivating your account means.\n   - Check the box to confirm your decision.\n   - Click **Deactivate**.\n\n### On Mobile App:\n1. **Open the Quora App**: Log in to your account if you aren\u2019t already.\n2. **Go to Settings**:\n   - Tap on your profile picture in the top-left corner.\n   - Scroll down and select **Settings**.\n3. **Deactivate Account**:\n   - Scroll down to the **Account** section.\n   - Tap on **Deactivate Account**.\n4. **Confirm Deactivation**:\n   - Read the prompts and confirm your decision.\n   - Tap **Deactivate**.\n\n### What Happens When You Deactivate:\n- Your profile, questions, answers, and other content will no longer be visible on Quora.\n- You can reactivate your account by logging in again within 14 days. After 14 days, your account and data may be permanently deleted.\n\nIf you have any issues or need further assistance, you can contact Quora support directly through their [Help Center](https://help.quora.com/hc/en-us).",
  "temperature": 1.0,
